<br>
Every year, right around this time, the old feeling flares up. Well, I get it other times of the year, at a varying frequency, but I can count on this feeling every day from mid-November until January.<br>
<br>
You know that feeling? It's so hard to get out of bed, because it feels like there's a 2 ton ACME weight on top of you.<br>
<br>
Or the inability to pay attention because you find yourself just staring off into space, musing on nothing except perhaps dust particles.<br>
<br>
Or the conflicting emotions - of wanting to be alone, but being tired of being so lonely. Wanting to be social, but wanting to be alone.<br>
<br>
Looking enviously at everyone else having a good time.. jealous of the couple at the mall, holding hands, sneaking the odd kiss. <br>
<br>
The painful memories - not painful because of the actual memories, but painful because they are in the past. Christmases with friends and family since dead, memories of christmas trees long gone, of presents broken and forgotten. <br>
<br>
*sighs*<br>
<br>
Is it January yet?<br>
